  const theoryContent = {
    "larmor-guide": {
      zh: { kicker: "EXPERIMENT 01 · GUIDE", title: "拉莫尔进动：实验导览", body: `
        <p class="theory-intro">这个实验研究一个具有磁矩 <i>μ</i> 的系统处在均匀、恒定磁场 <i>B</i> 中时的理想运动。重点不是记住一条公式，而是分清楚：哪些参数改变进动速度，哪些参数改变几何形状，哪些量在理想情况下保持不变。</p>
        <section class="theory-section"><h3>一、模型与假设</h3><ul><li>磁场在空间中均匀、随时间不变，因此只产生力矩，不讨论质心的 Stern–Gerlach 分束。</li><li>磁矩与角动量满足 <i>μ = γJ</i>，其中 γ 是带符号的旋磁比。</li><li>忽略阻尼、碰撞和辐射，所以系统不会逐渐“倒向”最低能量方向。</li></ul></section>
        <section class="theory-section"><h3>二、控制量分别做什么？</h3><table class="theory-table"><tr><th>控制量</th><th>你会看到的变化</th></tr><tr><td>磁场强度 B</td><td>改变角频率 ω<sub>L</sub>=|γ|B；B 加倍，周期减半。</td></tr><tr><td>旋磁比 γ</td><td>|γ| 控制快慢，γ 的符号控制进动方向。</td></tr><tr><td>初始夹角 θ₀</td><td>改变进动圆锥的开角与横向半径，不改变 ω<sub>L</sub>。</td></tr><tr><td>磁场方向</td><td>翻转进动轴，也会改变从固定观察方向判断出的旋转方向。</td></tr></table></section>
        <section class="theory-section"><h3>三、推荐的四步观察</h3><ol><li>先保持默认值，只拖动 θ₀，确认角度改变而频率基本不变。</li><li>把 B 从 1.5 T 改到 3.0 T，比较动画速度与周期读数。</li><li>反转 γ 的符号，观察轨道不变而运动方向反转。</li><li>令 γ=0 或 B=0，确认进动停止。</li></ol></section>
        <div class="theory-warning">常见误区：在这个无耗散模型中，磁矩不会自动与磁场对齐。要出现弛豫，需要额外加入与环境交换能量的机制。</div>` },
      en: { kicker: "EXPERIMENT 01 · GUIDE", title: "Larmor Precession: Lab Guide", body: `
        <p class="theory-intro">This lab studies the ideal motion of a magnetic moment <i>μ</i> in a uniform, static magnetic field <i>B</i>. The goal is to separate parameters that change the precession rate from those that change only its geometry.</p>
        <section class="theory-section"><h3>1. Model and assumptions</h3><ul><li>The field is spatially uniform and time independent, so it provides torque but no Stern–Gerlach center-of-mass splitting.</li><li>Magnetic moment and angular momentum obey <i>μ = γJ</i>, with a signed gyromagnetic ratio γ.</li><li>Damping, collisions, and radiation are neglected, so the moment does not relax toward the lowest-energy direction.</li></ul></section>
        <section class="theory-section"><h3>2. What does each control do?</h3><table class="theory-table"><tr><th>Control</th><th>Visible effect</th></tr><tr><td>Field B</td><td>Sets ω<sub>L</sub>=|γ|B; doubling B halves the period.</td></tr><tr><td>Gyromagnetic ratio γ</td><td>|γ| sets the speed, while its sign sets the sense of rotation.</td></tr><tr><td>Initial angle θ₀</td><td>Changes the cone angle and transverse radius, not ω<sub>L</sub>.</td></tr><tr><td>Field direction</td><td>Flips the precession axis and the apparent rotation from a fixed viewpoint.</td></tr></table></section>
        <section class="theory-section"><h3>3. Four suggested observations</h3><ol><li>Change only θ₀ and verify that geometry changes while frequency does not.</li><li>Double B from 1.5 T to 3.0 T and compare the animation with the period readout.</li><li>Reverse the sign of γ and watch the same orbit run in the opposite direction.</li><li>Set γ=0 or B=0 and verify that precession stops.</li></ol></section>
        <div class="theory-warning">Common misconception: without dissipation the moment does not align itself with the field. Relaxation requires an additional channel that exchanges energy with the environment.</div>` }
    },
    "larmor-derivation": {
      zh: { kicker: "EXPERIMENT 01 · DERIVATION", title: "拉莫尔进动：完整推导", body: `
        <p class="theory-intro">从磁场力矩出发，可以同时得到进动方程、角频率、守恒量和进动方向。下面不跳步地完成推导。</p>
        <div class="theory-step"><span>01</span><div><h4>磁场对磁矩施加力矩</h4><p>磁矩在磁场中的势能为 <i>U = −μ·B</i>。改变磁矩方向时，势能的角向变化给出力矩：</p><div class="theory-equation">τ = μ × B</div></div></div>
        <div class="theory-step"><span>02</span><div><h4>力矩改变角动量</h4><p>转动动力学关系是 <i>${mathFraction("dJ","dt","compact")} = τ</i>，再利用 <i>μ = γJ</i>：</p><div class="theory-equation">${mathFraction("dμ","dt")} = γ ${mathFraction("dJ","dt")} = γ μ × B</div></div></div>
        <div class="theory-step"><span>03</span><div><h4>把磁场取在 z 方向</h4><p>令 <i>B = Bẑ</i>。展开叉乘后得到三个分量方程：</p><div class="theory-equation">${mathFraction("dμ<sub>x</sub>","dt")} = γBμ<sub>y</sub>, &nbsp; ${mathFraction("dμ<sub>y</sub>","dt")} = −γBμ<sub>x</sub>, &nbsp; ${mathFraction("dμ<sub>z</sub>","dt")} = 0</div><p>所以纵向分量 μ<sub>z</sub> 不变，而横向两个分量彼此耦合。</p></div></div>
        <div class="theory-step"><span>04</span><div><h4>横向分量满足简谐方程</h4><p>对第一式再求一次时间导数，并代入第二式：</p><div class="theory-equation">${mathFraction("d²μ<sub>x</sub>","dt²")} = γB ${mathFraction("dμ<sub>y</sub>","dt")} = −(γB)² μ<sub>x</sub></div><p>μ<sub>y</sub> 同样满足角频率为 |γ|B 的简谐方程。</p></div></div>
        <div class="theory-step"><span>05</span><div><h4>写出轨迹与拉莫尔频率</h4><div class="theory-equation amber">μ<sub>x</sub>=μ⊥cos(ω<sub>L</sub>t+φ₀), &nbsp; μ<sub>y</sub>=−sgn(γ)μ⊥sin(ω<sub>L</sub>t+φ₀)</div><div class="theory-equation">ω<sub>L</sub>=|γ|B, &nbsp; T<sub>L</sub>=${mathFraction("2π","|γ|B")}</div><p>γ 的绝对值进入频率；γ 的符号只出现在正弦项前，从而决定旋转方向。</p></div></div>
        <div class="theory-step"><span>06</span><div><h4>验证两个守恒量</h4><div class="theory-equation">${mathFraction("d|μ|²","dt")} = 2μ·(γμ×B)=0</div><div class="theory-equation">${mathFraction("d(μ·B)","dt")} = γ(μ×B)·B=0</div><p>因此 |μ| 与 μ·B 都不变，磁矩和磁场之间的夹角 θ 也保持不变。势能 U=−μ·B 同样守恒。</p></div></div>
        <div class="theory-note">几何图像：${mathFraction("dμ","dt","compact")} 始终同时垂直于 μ 和 B，它只能沿圆锥切向推动磁矩，而不能改变磁矩长度或锥角。</div>` },
      en: { kicker: "EXPERIMENT 01 · DERIVATION", title: "Larmor Precession: Full Derivation", body: `
        <p class="theory-intro">Starting from magnetic torque, we can derive the equation of motion, frequency, conserved quantities, and direction of precession without skipping steps.</p>
        <div class="theory-step"><span>01</span><div><h4>Magnetic torque</h4><p>The potential energy is <i>U=−μ·B</i>. Its angular variation gives:</p><div class="theory-equation">τ = μ × B</div></div></div>
        <div class="theory-step"><span>02</span><div><h4>Torque changes angular momentum</h4><p>Use <i>${mathFraction("dJ","dt","compact")}=τ</i> and <i>μ=γJ</i>:</p><div class="theory-equation">${mathFraction("dμ","dt")} = γ ${mathFraction("dJ","dt")} = γ μ × B</div></div></div>
        <div class="theory-step"><span>03</span><div><h4>Choose B along z</h4><div class="theory-equation">${mathFraction("dμ<sub>x</sub>","dt")} = γBμ<sub>y</sub>, &nbsp; ${mathFraction("dμ<sub>y</sub>","dt")} = −γBμ<sub>x</sub>, &nbsp; ${mathFraction("dμ<sub>z</sub>","dt")} = 0</div><p>The longitudinal component stays fixed while the transverse components are coupled.</p></div></div>
        <div class="theory-step"><span>04</span><div><h4>Harmonic transverse motion</h4><div class="theory-equation">${mathFraction("d²μ<sub>x</sub>","dt²")} = −(γB)² μ<sub>x</sub></div><p>The same equation holds for μ<sub>y</sub>.</p></div></div>
        <div class="theory-step"><span>05</span><div><h4>Trajectory and frequency</h4><div class="theory-equation amber">μ<sub>x</sub>=μ⊥cos(ω<sub>L</sub>t+φ₀), &nbsp; μ<sub>y</sub>=−sgn(γ)μ⊥sin(ω<sub>L</sub>t+φ₀)</div><div class="theory-equation">ω<sub>L</sub>=|γ|B, &nbsp; T<sub>L</sub>=${mathFraction("2π","|γ|B")}</div><p>The magnitude of γ sets the rate; its sign sets the sense of rotation.</p></div></div>
        <div class="theory-step"><span>06</span><div><h4>Conserved quantities</h4><div class="theory-equation">${mathFraction("d|μ|²","dt")} = 2μ·(γμ×B)=0</div><div class="theory-equation">${mathFraction("d(μ·B)","dt")} = γ(μ×B)·B=0</div><p>Thus |μ|, μ·B, the cone angle θ, and the energy U=−μ·B are constant.</p></div></div>
        <div class="theory-note">Geometrically, ${mathFraction("dμ","dt","compact")} is perpendicular to both μ and B. It pushes the moment along the cone rather than changing its length or opening angle.</div>` }
    },
    "sg-guide": {
      zh: { kicker: "EXPERIMENT 02–03 · GUIDE", title: "Stern–Gerlach：实验导览", body: `
        <p class="theory-intro">Stern–Gerlach 实验把内部量子自由度转化成空间中可见的分束。它最重要的结构不是“磁场很强”，而是磁场必须具有空间梯度。</p>
        <section class="theory-section"><h3>一、装置从左到右</h3><ol><li><b>银原子炉：</b>产生近似未偏振的中性银原子束。</li><li><b>准直狭缝：</b>压窄初始位置与速度方向，使后续分束能被分辨。</li><li><b>非均匀磁场：</b>把磁矩沿测量轴的分量转化为不同的横向力。</li><li><b>探测屏：</b>记录每个原子的落点，许多离散事件逐渐形成两个斑点。</li></ol></section>
        <section class="theory-section"><h3>二、为什么均匀磁场不够？</h3><p>均匀磁场会让磁矩发生拉莫尔进动，但对一个小磁偶极子的整体平动力，正负两端受到的作用会相互抵消。要让质心发生可分辨偏转，需要：</p><div class="theory-equation">F<sub>n</sub> ≈ μ<sub>n</sub> ${mathFraction("∂B","∂n")}</div></section>
        <section class="theory-section"><h3>三、两个模式分别观察什么？</h3><table class="theory-table"><tr><th>模式</th><th>核心问题</th></tr><tr><td>基础分束</td><td>为什么经典连续取向没有产生连续条纹，而只出现两种离散结果？</td></tr><tr><td>串联测量</td><td>为什么插入不同方向的分析器，会改变之后再次测量 z 时的统计？</td></tr></table></section>
        <section class="theory-section"><h3>四、建议操作</h3><ol><li>用未偏振束旋转 α，确认两支概率始终各为 ${mathFraction("1","2","compact")}。</li><li>选择 +z 入射态：α=0° 时结果确定，α=90° 时变为 50∶50。</li><li>调节磁场梯度，确认它只改变斑点间距，不改变概率。</li><li>进入串联模式，依次比较 z→z 和 z→x(+)→z。</li></ol></section>
        <div class="theory-warning">图中的粒子运动速度与装置尺寸采用教学标度；概率关系、支路计数与角度依赖才是需要读取的物理量。</div>` },
      en: { kicker: "EXPERIMENT 02–03 · GUIDE", title: "Stern–Gerlach: Lab Guide", body: `
        <p class="theory-intro">The Stern–Gerlach experiment converts an internal quantum degree of freedom into visible spatial splitting. The essential feature is not merely a strong field, but a spatial field gradient.</p>
        <section class="theory-section"><h3>1. Apparatus from left to right</h3><ol><li><b>Silver oven:</b> produces an approximately unpolarized neutral atomic beam.</li><li><b>Collimator:</b> narrows the initial position and direction.</li><li><b>Nonuniform field:</b> converts a magnetic-moment component into a transverse force.</li><li><b>Detector:</b> records individual arrivals that build two spots.</li></ol></section>
        <section class="theory-section"><h3>2. Why is a uniform field insufficient?</h3><p>A uniform field produces Larmor precession, but not a resolved center-of-mass force. Spatial deflection requires:</p><div class="theory-equation">F<sub>n</sub> ≈ μ<sub>n</sub> ${mathFraction("∂B","∂n")}</div></section>
        <section class="theory-section"><h3>3. What do the two modes ask?</h3><table class="theory-table"><tr><th>Mode</th><th>Core question</th></tr><tr><td>Beam splitting</td><td>Why do classical continuous orientations produce only two quantum outcomes?</td></tr><tr><td>Sequential measurement</td><td>Why does an intermediate analyzer alter the statistics of a later z measurement?</td></tr></table></section>
        <section class="theory-section"><h3>4. Suggested procedure</h3><ol><li>Rotate α for an unpolarized beam and verify that both outcomes stay at ${mathFraction("1","2","compact")}.</li><li>Prepare +z: α=0° is deterministic, while α=90° gives 50∶50.</li><li>Change the gradient and verify that it changes separation, not probability.</li><li>Compare z→z with z→x(+)→z in sequential mode.</li></ol></section>
        <div class="theory-warning">Particle speed and apparatus size use teaching scales. Probability relations, counts, and angular dependence are the physically meaningful readouts.</div>` }
    },
    "sg-derivation": {
      zh: { kicker: "EXPERIMENT 02–03 · DERIVATION", title: "Stern–Gerlach：从力到概率", body: `
        <p class="theory-intro">推导分成两部分：磁场梯度负责把不同磁矩分量分开；量子态与测量本征态的重叠负责决定每条支路的概率。</p>
        <div class="theory-step"><span>01</span><div><h4>磁偶极子的能量与力</h4><div class="theory-equation">U = −μ·B, &nbsp; F = −∇U = ∇(μ·B)</div><p>若装置主要沿 n 方向变化，且原子进入磁铁后近似绝热地跟随测量轴：</p><div class="theory-equation">F<sub>n</sub> ≈ μ<sub>n</sub> ${mathFraction("∂B","∂n")}</div></div></div>
        <div class="theory-step"><span>02</span><div><h4>自旋 ½ 只有两个本征值</h4><p>沿单位方向 n̂<sub>α</sub> 测量自旋，对应算符：</p><div class="theory-equation">S<sub>α</sub> = ${mathFraction("ℏ","2")} σ·n̂<sub>α</sub></div><p>它的本征值只有 +${mathFraction("ℏ","2","compact")} 和 −${mathFraction("ℏ","2","compact")}，因此磁矩投影也只有两个允许值，最终形成两条支路。</p></div></div>
        <div class="theory-step"><span>03</span><div><h4>半角概率从态重叠得到</h4><p>设入射纯态沿 θ 方向为 |+θ⟩，分析器沿 α。自旋旋量之间的重叠给出：</p><div class="theory-equation amber">P(+α)=|⟨+α|+θ⟩|²=cos²(${mathFraction("θ−α","2")})</div><div class="theory-equation">P(−α)=sin²(${mathFraction("θ−α","2")})</div><p>这里出现半角而不是普通矢量投影的 cos²(θ−α)，正是自旋 ½ 几何的特征。</p></div></div>
        <div class="theory-step"><span>04</span><div><h4>未偏振束为何总是 50∶50？</h4><p>未偏振态用密度矩阵 ρ=${mathFraction("I","2","compact")} 表示。对任意分析方向：</p><div class="theory-equation">P(±α)=Tr[ρ |±α⟩⟨±α|]=${mathFraction("1","2")}</div><p>所以旋转分析器只旋转两条空间支路的方向，不会改变各自的总人数。</p></div></div>
        <div class="theory-step"><span>05</span><div><h4>选择支路就是重新制备状态</h4><p>第一台 SG<sub>z</sub> 从未偏振束中保留 +z 后，传输率为 ${mathFraction("1","2","compact")}。中间分析器沿 α 并保留 +α：</p><div class="theory-equation">P(+α|+z)=cos²(${mathFraction("α","2")})</div><p>通过选择器后的原子不再处于 +z，而处于新的 |+α⟩。</p></div></div>
        <div class="theory-step"><span>06</span><div><h4>第三台分析器的条件概率</h4><div class="theory-equation">P(+β|+α)=cos²(${mathFraction("β−α","2")})</div><p>因此每 100 个最初未偏振原子，最后进入 +β 支路的期望数为：</p><div class="theory-equation">N<sub>+β</sub>=100×${mathFraction("1","2")}×cos²(${mathFraction("α","2")})×cos²(${mathFraction("β−α","2")})</div></div></div>
        <section class="theory-section"><h3>检验 z → x(+) → z</h3><p>取 α=90°、β=0°。第一台选出 +z 留下 50 个；中间 +x 支路留下其中一半，即 25 个；最后测 z 又各分一半：</p><div class="theory-equation amber">N<sub>+z</sub>=12.5, &nbsp; N<sub>−z</sub>=12.5</div><p>这说明 x 测量不是偷偷“读出”一个原先就存在的 x 分量，而是改变了可用于后续预测的量子态。</p></section>
        <div class="theory-note">与拉莫尔进动的连接：均匀磁场控制自旋态在两次测量之间的相位演化；非均匀磁场把最终的自旋投影转化成空间分束。以后加入 Ramsey/Rabi 模块时，这两部分会合并起来。</div>` },
      en: { kicker: "EXPERIMENT 02–03 · DERIVATION", title: "Stern–Gerlach: From Force to Probability", body: `
        <p class="theory-intro">The derivation has two layers: the field gradient spatially separates magnetic-moment components, while quantum-state overlaps determine the probability of each branch.</p>
        <div class="theory-step"><span>01</span><div><h4>Energy and force of a magnetic dipole</h4><div class="theory-equation">U = −μ·B, &nbsp; F = −∇U = ∇(μ·B)</div><div class="theory-equation">F<sub>n</sub> ≈ μ<sub>n</sub> ${mathFraction("∂B","∂n")}</div></div></div>
        <div class="theory-step"><span>02</span><div><h4>A spin-½ observable has two eigenvalues</h4><div class="theory-equation">S<sub>α</sub> = ${mathFraction("ℏ","2")} σ·n̂<sub>α</sub></div><p>Its eigenvalues are only +${mathFraction("ℏ","2","compact")} and −${mathFraction("ℏ","2","compact")}, so the magnetic-moment projection and spatial force have only two allowed outcomes.</p></div></div>
        <div class="theory-step"><span>03</span><div><h4>Half-angle probabilities</h4><div class="theory-equation amber">P(+α)=|⟨+α|+θ⟩|²=cos²(${mathFraction("θ−α","2")})</div><div class="theory-equation">P(−α)=sin²(${mathFraction("θ−α","2")})</div><p>The half angle, rather than an ordinary vector projection, is characteristic of spin-½ geometry.</p></div></div>
        <div class="theory-step"><span>04</span><div><h4>Why is an unpolarized beam always 50∶50?</h4><div class="theory-equation">ρ=${mathFraction("I","2")}, &nbsp; P(±α)=Tr[ρ |±α⟩⟨±α|]=${mathFraction("1","2")}</div><p>Rotating the analyzer rotates the spatial branches but does not change their populations.</p></div></div>
        <div class="theory-step"><span>05</span><div><h4>Branch selection prepares a new state</h4><div class="theory-equation">P(+α|+z)=cos²(${mathFraction("α","2")})</div><p>After selecting +α, the beam is in |+α⟩ rather than its earlier +z state.</p></div></div>
        <div class="theory-step"><span>06</span><div><h4>The final conditional probability</h4><div class="theory-equation">P(+β|+α)=cos²(${mathFraction("β−α","2")})</div><div class="theory-equation">N<sub>+β</sub>=100×${mathFraction("1","2")}×cos²(${mathFraction("α","2")})×cos²(${mathFraction("β−α","2")})</div></div></div>
        <section class="theory-section"><h3>Check z → x(+) → z</h3><p>With α=90° and β=0°, the first selector leaves 50 atoms, the +x selector leaves 25, and the final z analyzer splits those equally:</p><div class="theory-equation amber">N<sub>+z</sub>=12.5, &nbsp; N<sub>−z</sub>=12.5</div><p>The x measurement does not merely reveal a pre-existing x component; it changes the state used for later predictions.</p></section>
        <div class="theory-note">Connection to Larmor precession: a uniform field controls phase evolution between measurements, while a nonuniform field converts the final spin projection into spatial splitting.</div>` }
    }
  };

